<h2>What is Space Python? </h2>
<p>Space Python is a fun and interactive platform to learn and practice Python coding. This platform was created with the purpose of encouraging students to develop their Python knowledge. Using a mix of lessons, interactive activities, and engaging projects, we encourage kids to develop their python coding knowledge. Our curriculum is built for students aged 11-14, but can be enjoyed by a variety of ages. Start your mission with us today by clicking the "Log In!" or "Sign Up!" buttons. </p>

<h2>Our Curriculum: </h2>
<p>We begin each lesson by either introducing students to a new concept in Python coding or building on a concept that they have learned before.  Students are able to see a problem solved before solving a problem that is similar so that they fully understand the steps involved. Students solve smaller problems before solving more complex problems to create a deeper sense of understanding while progressing through topics. After each unit, students will review the unit then test their knowledge with a quiz and a unit challenge project. Both students and their parents can view the student's progress through the Space Python Curriculum.</p>
<p>Learn more about our curriculum on the <a href="/about">About</a> page.</p>

